    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the federally recognized Pit River Tribe. The Pit River Tribe is comprised of eleven separate bands: Ajumawi, Atsugewi, Atwamsini, Ilmawi, Astarawi, Hammawi, Hewisedawi, Itsatawi, Aporige, Kosalektawi, and Madesi. The indigenous homeland of the Pit River Tribe is spread across the California counties of Shasta, Siskiyou, Modoc, and Lassen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
